================================================================================
Color palettes / theme variants — attribution (v3, post cross-review)
================================================================================

The framework ships 16 theme variants. The first reproduces the canonical
Dracula Theme palette by Zeno Rocha (MIT) and is kept as the framework's
historical root. Drakul is an AA-compliant sibling of Dracula. The other 14
are original works by Julien Bombled, released under Apache 2.0, engineered
with the "Geometric Color Palette" / uniform-Oklab-L* philosophy and
cross-reviewed by four independent audit passes (an independent reviewer, an independent reviewer, an independent reviewer).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Dracula Theme — MIT (Zeno Rocha)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  - Dracula        Dracula Theme    (MIT)
                   https://github.com/dracula/dracula-theme

  Note : the canonical Dracula palette has a historical accessibility
  shortcoming — Comment color #6272A4 ratios to 3.03 vs Background and 1.94
  vs CurrentLine, both below WCAG 2.1 AA 4.5:1 threshold. We preserve the
  variant unchanged for canonical fidelity. See variant Drakul (below) for
  the AA-compliant sibling.

  - Drakul         Apache 2.0 — Julien Bombled
                   Derivative of the canonical Dracula Theme palette with
                   Comment slot lifted from #6272A4 to #B3BBD6 to clear
                   WCAG AA (Comment/CL = 4.79, Comment/Bg = 7.46). Every
                   other slot byte-identical to Dracula. Named after Vlad II
                   Dracul (~1395-1447), member of the Societas Draconistarum
                   (Order of the Dragon, 1408), historical father of Vlad III
                   Țepeș from whom Stoker derived "Dracula". Public domain.

